org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.consed.phd

Interface PhdBallVisitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPhdBallVisitor

    public interface PhdBallVisitor
    PhdBallVisitor is a visitor for a phd.ball file or phd file that contains one or more phd records.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

    • Method Detail

      • visitFileComment

        void visitFileComment(String comment)
        Optional comment at the beginning of new versions of phd.ball files. The comment is often the path to the corresponding wrapped input file (path to fastq or sff file).
        Parameters:
        comment - the comment at the beginning of the phd file.

      • visitPhd

        PhdVisitor visitPhd(PhdBallVisitorCallback callback,
                    String id,
                    Integer version)
        Denotes when a new phd record has been detected.
        Parameters:
        callback - the PhdBallVisitorCallback instance that can be used to call pack to the parser.
        id - the id of this phd record.
        version - the version of this phd record; if the version is not specified, then this value will be null. More recent versions of the phdball file format specification allow the version to be included for each record but not all files contain this information.
        Returns:
        a non-null PhdVisitor instance if this record should be parsed; or null if this phd record should be skipped.

      • visitEnd

        void visitEnd()
        The phd file has been completely visited.

      • halted

        void halted()
        The phd visitation has been halted, usually by calling PhdBallVisitorCallback.haltParsing().
